      <h1 class="display-1">How to Become a Loan Processor</h1>
      <p class="lead hero-subtitle">A loan processor is the organized engine behind every closing &mdash; assembling and verifying the loan file so deals get done. It's an accessible entry point into the mortgage business, often with no licensing exam required, and a common stepping stone to licensed origination.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="#role" class="btn btn-primary btn-large">What the Role Involves</a>
        <a href="#path" class="btn btn-secondary btn-large">How to Get In</a>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-trust">
        <span class="trust-dot"></span><span>Jim Blackburn &middot; NMLS #1072866</span>
        <span class="trust-dot"></span><span>7&times; Scotsman Guide Top Producer</span>
        <span class="trust-dot"></span><span>$500M+ Closed</span>
      </div>
    </div>
